Description: Accu-Chek®SoftclixSo gentle, it’s virtually painless1.Accu-Chek® Softclix is specifically designed to take the pain out of everyday testing. The features of the Accu-Chek® Softclix make it a high-quality lancing device. Features include:One-hand primingUser-friendly design. The pen like style make it discreet and easy to handle.Proven virtually pain free1 Discreet. Pen-like designVirtually pain free. High-speed precise motion with active needle retraction. Clixmotion technology guides the lancet movement preventing needle oscillation and unnecessary tissue damage.Personalised comfort. 11 depth settings so you can choose the most comfortable setting to suit your skin type.Hygienic and simple. New, unused Accu-Chek® lancets are sterile and the device is designed so that the lancet can be discarded without the need to touch it.Suitable for alternate site testing with AST capAlternative site testing is not recommended in all circumstances and may not be suitable for all people with diabetes. Refer to your healthcare professional for advice.Specifications for Device:Adjustable Penetration Depth Setting: 11 settings, comfort dialPenetration Range: 0.8 to 2.3 mmWeight: 21 gSpecifications for Lancet:Needle Diameter: 0.4 mmSilicon Coated: YesLancet refills: Available in boxes of 100, 200The Accu-Chek® Softclix lancing device is simple to operate, due to the one-hand priming and pen-like design.Pull off the cap on the lancing device. Insert a new lancet into the lancet holder and push it in until it clicks. Twist off the lancets’ protective cover to expose the point. Press the Accu-Chek® Softclix cap on again until it clicks. Check that you have the Comfort Dial at the desired penetration depth. Press the priming button until it clicks. Gently press Accu-Chek®Softclix against the side of the fingertip and press the yellow release button. After measuring your blood glucose, pull off the Softclix cap and slide the ejector forwards to remove the lancet.Treat fingertips with care by using lancets only once. Sharpness diminishes with repeated use, a fresh lancet is recommended every time you test. Using a sharp lancet and using a different fingertip each time you test will help minimise tissue damage and callus formation. Combine this with the patented Clixmotion technology from Accu-Chek®, and you can be assured of especially gentle and virtually pain-free blood sampling.
